            . I live at Edmonton. This box is Mr. Johnson's property, and contains these articles.</p>
               <p>DODSON's Defence. The box was on the pavement in St. Martin's-le-Grand - a man asked me to carry it to the Bell public-house, Foster-lane; when I got to the corner of the lane I missed him, and asked this man to mind it for me, while I looked for him.</p>
               <p>PRETTY's Defence. He asked me to mind the box - I said Yes, if he would not belong.</p>
